cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques, specifically deep convolutional networks, for medical image analysis. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the use of neural networks for feature learning and classification falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application areas mentioned in the abstract, such as segmentation and retrieval, also suggest the multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the use of deep learning techniques implies the use of optimization algorithms, which falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) category.
